.TH FIDO2LUKS-EXTENDED 8 "2026-05-13" "fido2luks-extended 1.0.0" "System Administration"

.SH NAME
fido2luks\-extended \- unlock LUKS volumes at boot using a FIDO2 token

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fido2luks\-extended

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fido2luks\-extended
is an initramfs-tools extension for unlocking LUKS encrypted volumes at boot
time using a FIDO2 token, such as a YubiKey or Nitrokey.

It installs an initramfs hook and a cryptsetup keyscript that allow a LUKS2
volume enrolled with a systemd FIDO2 token to be unlocked during early boot.

The keyscript supports Plymouth bootsplash integration and uses
.BR fido2-token (1),
.BR fido2-assert (1),
.BR jq (1),
and
.BR cryptsetup (8)
inside the initramfs environment.

If FIDO2 unlocking fails, the script falls back to asking for the recovery
LUKS passphrase.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B /etc/initramfs-tools/hooks/fido2luks-extended
Initramfs hook that copies required binaries into the initramfs image.

.TP
.B /lib/fido2luks-extended/keyscript.sh
Cryptsetup keyscript used during initramfs boot.

.TP
.B /usr/share/doc/fido2luks-extended/README.md
Package documentation.

.SH CONFIGURATION
The keyscript supports the following environment variables:

.TP
.B FIDO2LUKS_DEBUG
Set to
.B 1
to enable technical debug messages. Defaults to
.BR 0 .

.TP
.B FIDO2LUKS_LANG
Language for user-facing messages. Supported values are
.B en
and
.BR sl .
Defaults to
.BR en .

.TP
.B FIDO2LUKS_WAIT_SECONDS
How long to wait for the FIDO2 USB key to appear during initramfs boot.
Defaults to
.BR 15 .

.TP
.B FIDO2LUKS_TOUCH_SECONDS
How long to wait for user-presence touch confirmation.
Defaults to
.BR 20 .

.SH SETUP
The following commands should be run as root.

To set an initial FIDO2 PIN, run:

.EX
fido2-token -S /dev/hidraw1
.EE

To enroll the FIDO2 device with LUKS2, run:

.EX
systemd-cryptenroll --fido2-device=auto \\
  --fido2-with-client-pin=true \\
  --fido2-with-user-presence=true \\
  /dev/nvme0n1p5
.EE

In this example, the LUKS device is assumed to be:

.EX
/dev/nvme0n1p5
.EE

To configure
.BR crypttab (5)
to use the keyscript for a mapping named
.BR nvme0n1p5_crypt ,
run:

.EX
sed -i \\
  '/^nvme0n1p5_crypt /{
    /keyscript=/! s#$#,keyscript=/lib/fido2luks-extended/keyscript.sh#
    s#keyscript=[^, ]*#keyscript=/lib/fido2luks-extended/keyscript.sh#
  }' \\
  /etc/crypttab
.EE

After installation or configuration changes, regenerate initramfs:

.EX
update-initramfs -u -k all
.EE

.SH DEPENDENCIES
This package depends on
.BR initramfs-tools ,
.BR cryptsetup-initramfs ,
.BR fido2-tools ,
and
.BR jq .

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR crypttab (5),
.BR cryptsetup (8),
.BR systemd-cryptenroll (1),
.BR fido2-token (1),
.BR fido2-assert (1),
.BR update-initramfs (8)

